<datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="520">
<subfield code="a">
Collection of the archival video of the entire repertories of four master storytellers, Dai Buzhang, Fei Zhengliang (Fei Li), Gao Zaihua, and Ren Jitang (Ren Dekun) were recorded on video for the project "Large-scale Registration of Chinese Storytelling" from 2001 to 2003 in Yangzhou. In addition, a medium-length repertoire was told by Ren Dekun. Project co-leaders were Fei Li and Vibeke Børdahl, project assistant, co-editor and translator was Huang Ying, Yangzhou University; photographers were Li Xin and Chen Wei, Yangzhou. Yangzhou storytelling (Yangzhou pinghua) is oral narrative, primarily in Yangzhou dialect, performed with gestures and learned through apprenticeship with a professional master storyteller.
</subfield>
</datafield>
<datafield ind1="0" ind2=" " tag="505">
<subfield code="a">
Dai school of Journey to the west / Dai Buzhang (MV001-MV100) -- Wu school of Three kingdoms / Fei Zhengliang (MV101-MV150) -- Kang school of Three kingdoms / Gao Zaihua (MV151-MV260) -- Wang school of Water margin / Ren Jitang (MV261-MV348) -- Emperor Qian Long goes south / Ren Dekun (MV349-MV360)
</subfield>
</datafield>
<datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="500">
<subfield code="a">
Fei Zhengliang is the artistic name for Fei Li; Ren Jitang is the artistic name for Ren Dekun.
</subfield>
</datafield>
